    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I know there are many of us who, when you don&#8217;t post for awhile, wonder how you&#8217;re doing, and are glad to know things are okay. But while buttermilk biscuits weren&#8217;t today&#8217;s subject, if you haven&#8217;t discovered it yet, you must try Grace Harbor buttermilk. The farm is in Lynden, and I buy their products at either Ballard or Central Market.  OMG, it&#8217;s so good, I could drink it by itself. It makes the best ranch-style dressing I&#8217;ve ever tasted. The first time I tried it, I was reminded of tasting butter in England decades ago.  And now, in a roundabout way, you&#8217;ve given me a dinner inspiration. I have just enough left to make either ranch dressing or biscuits!</p>
    </div>

